{"url": "https://www.elle.com.au/fashion/bella-hadid-ugly-sneakers-14776", "text": "If there's one thing Bella Hadid knows how to do, it's how to make trends work for her.\n\nA quick look at her street-style game in the past six months shows that the 21-year-old bounces from trend to trend like a fashionable long-legged tennis ball. One day she's sleek and slick at a Bulgari gala, the next she's in sweatpants, a crop top and a bomber, after that she's in a lace mini-dress and a Dior beret that wouldn't look out of place on the set of a Jean-Luc Godard film.\n\nThe most recent trend Ms Bella has plucked from the runways and thrust into our Instagram Explore pages is the ugly sneaker.\n\nSeveral times over the past couple of months, the 21-year-old has stepped out wearing a perfectly chic outfit paired with a pair of fairly ugly trainers-and not even in a 'commuter chic' way.\n\nHere, of course, we mean 'ugly' in the affectionate sense. Balenciaga, Acne and New Balance have been steering sneaker-shaped shoewear trends back from 'sleek and sexy' (see: Gucci, Stan Smiths, and Common Projects), back to its original-and most powerful-form: BBQ Dad appropriate.\n\nYou know the ones: bulky, over-detailed, sporting a thick sole, a tennis-shoe toe, and round laces? The ones your uncool uncle used to wear with his khaki trousers and faded polo shirts? Yeah, those.\n\nExcept, under Bella's expert styling, the sneakers add a sense of levity and fun into her outfit. They say 'I'm trying just the right amount, and you know it,' and 'You'll never figure out if I'm being serious or not,' all in one.", "images": ["https://d3lp4xedbqa8a5.cloudfront.net/s3/digital-cougar-assets/elle/2017/10/26/1508997511737_GettyImages-825679320master.jpg?width=690&height=&mode=crop&quality=75", "https://d3lp4xedbqa8a5.cloudfront.net/s3/digital-cougar-assets/Elle/2021/06/15/25410/rollasjeans_200333033_2438560162954132_8962061753324004911_n.jpg?width=170&height=105&mode=crop&quality=75", "https://www.el